          Before allowing anyone into your home, confirm the company carries liability insurance and is bonded. This is especially important in Birmingham's premium neighborhoods where a single accident could mean significant damage. <strong>Ask directly:</strong> "Can you provide proof of insurance?"
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 2: Read Local Reviews (Not Just Star Ratings)</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Look for reviews on Google and Facebook from people in your specific area of Birmingham. A company that does great work in Hoover might not serve Trussville as well. Pay attention to comments about reliability and consistency.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 3: Ask About Their Cleaning Process</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Professional companies should be able to explain exactly what's included in their service. Request a written checklist so you know what to expect and can hold them accountable.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 4: Get Pricing in Writing</h3>
